   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>Subject One Hundred Seventy-six SEPARATED AND ALIENATED FROM GOD Scripture: Col 1:21 Separated from God Man was originally created by God; he belonged to God and lived before God.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>Due to his sin, man was separated from God.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Not only is there a barrier between man and God, but there is also a distance between the two.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Alienated from God Not only is man separated from God passively, but he is also alienated from Him actively.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Separation from God is a forsaking of God, but alienation is a rebellion against God.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Separation is a departure from God, but alienation is an assault upon God.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>The life of man today is not merely one that is separated from God, but it is one that is daily antagonistic toward God.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Use examples to prove this.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>How to be reconciled to God Confess that you are separated and alienated from God.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Repent to God.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>Believe in Jesus Christ, the Son of God, as Savior.</S>
   </TEXT>
